						<summary>

						<p>Slab kept in the courtyard of the Īśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>10th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged and worn out inscription is in characters of about 10th century A.D. Introduces two chiefs of the Kiḷḷa family Kannayya and his brother Vikramāditya, who bore the title Mūlapuraparamēśvara.</p>						

